  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<title>Overfitting Demo — Polynomial Regression</title>\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\">\n<style>\n  body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, Arial; margin: 18px; color: #111; }\n  h1 { margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 20px; }\n  p { margin: 6px 0 14px 0; color: #333; max-width: 760px; }\n  .controls { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; align-items:center; margin-bottom:12px; }\n  label { font-size:13px; color:#222; }\n  input[type=range] { width:160px; vertical-align:middle; margin-left:8px; }\n  input[type=number] { width:72px; margin-left:8px; }\n  button { padding:8px 12px; background:#2b79ff; color:white; border:0; border-radius:6px; cursor:pointer; }\n  button.secondary { background:#e9eefb; color:#1b2b4a; }\n  #canvasWrap { border:1px solid #ddd; width:820px; background:white; padding:12px; border-radius:8px; }\n  canvas { display:block; background:linear-gradient(#fff, #fbfdff); }\n  .metrics { margin-top:10px; display:flex; gap:18px; flex-wrap:wrap; align-items:center; }\n  .metric { font-size:14px; color:#111; background:#f6f9ff; padding:8px 10px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #e5eefc; }\n  .small { font-size:12px; color:#444; }\n  .footer { margin-top:12px; max-width:760px; color:#333; font-size:13px; }\n  .controls-group { display:flex; gap:6px; align-items:center; }\n  .checkbox { transform:translateY(1px); margin-left:8px; }\n  @media (max-width:860px){ #canvasWrap, canvas{ width:100%; } }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Overfitting (Interactive Demo)</h1>\n<p>\n  This interactive visualization shows how polynomial models can underfit, fit well, or overfit data.\n  Generate noisy samples from a fixed \"true\" function, fit a polynomial of adjustable degree, and compare\n  training vs test error. Increase degree too far and the model will follow noise — that is overfitting.\n</p>\n\n<div class=\"controls\">\n  <div class=\"controls-group\">\n    <label>Degree: <span id=\"degVal\">3</span></label>\n    <input id=\"degree\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"20\" value=\"3\">\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"controls-group\">\n    <label>Samples:</label>\n    <input id=\"nSamples\" type=\"range\" min=\"6\" max=\"200\" value=\"30\">\n    <span id=\"nSamplesVal\" class=\"small\">30</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"controls-group\">\n    <label>Noise σ:</label>\n    <input id=\"noise\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"1.5\" step=\"0.01\" value=\"0.2\">\n    <span id=\"noiseVal\" class=\"small\">0.20</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"controls-group\">\n    <label>Train %:</label>\n    <input id=\"trainPct\" type=\"range\" min=\"30\" max=\"90\" value=\"70\">\n    <span id=\"trainPctVal\" class=\"small\">70%</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"controls-group\">\n    <label>Ridge λ:</label>\n    <input id=\"lambda\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"0.01\" value=\"0\">\n    <span id=\"lambdaVal\" class=\"small\">0.00</span>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-left:auto; display:flex; gap:8px;\">\n    <button id=\"regen\">Regenerate</button>\n    <button id=\"reset\" class=\"secondary\">Reset</button>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"canvasWrap\">\n  <canvas id=\"plot\" width=\"800\" height=\"360\"></canvas>\n  <div class=\"metrics\">\n    <div class=\"metric\">Training MSE: <strong id=\"trainMse\">-</strong></div>\n    <div class=\"metric\">Test MSE: <strong id=\"testMse\">-</strong></div>\n    <div class=\"metric small\">Green = fitted curve • Blue = train points • Red = test points • Gray = true function</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"footer\">\n  Tip: move the Degree slider. With few samples and high degree you'll see the curve wiggle dramatically to pass through training points — high training accuracy but poor test performance = overfitting. Increasing λ (ridge) smooths the fit.\n</div>\n\n<script>\n// ==== Utilities: simple linear algebra ====\nfunction transpose(A) {\n  const m = A.length, n = A[0].length;\n  const T = Array.from({length:n},()=>Array(m));\n  for(let i=0;i<m;i++) for(let j=0;j<n;j++) T[j][i]=A[i][j];\n  return T;\n}\nfunction matMul(A,B) {\n  const m=A.length, p=A[0].length, n=B[0].length;\n  const C=Array.from({length:m},()=>Array(n).fill(0));\n  for(let i=0;i<m;i++) for(let k=0;k<p;k++){\n    const aik=A[i][k];\n    for(let j=0;j<n;j++) C[i][j]+=aik*B[k][j];\n  }\n  return C;\n}\nfunction vecDot(a,b){ let s=0; for(let i=0;i<a.length;i++) s+=a[i]*b[i]; return s; }\nfunction matVecMul(A,v){ const m=A.length, n=A[0].length; const out=Array(m).fill(0); for(let i=0;i<m;i++){ let s=0; for(let j=0;j<n;j++) s+=A[i][j]*v[j]; out[i]=s;} return out; }\nfunction addDiag(A,mu){ const n=A.length; const B=A.map((row,i)=>row.slice()); for(let i=0;i<n;i++) B[i][i]+=mu; return B; }\n\n// Solve linear system Ax = b using Gaussian elimination with partial pivoting (A is square)\nfunction solveLinear(Ain, bin) {\n  const n = Ain.length;\n  const A = Ain.map(r=>r.slice());\n  const b = bin.slice();\n  for(let k=0;k<n;k++){\n    // pivot\n    let pivot = k;\n    let maxv = Math.abs(A[k][k]);\n    for(let i=k+1;i<n;i++){\n      const av = Math.abs(A[i][k]);\n      if(av > maxv){ maxv=av; pivot=i; }\n    }\n    if(maxv < 1e-12) { // singular or nearly\n      // regularize a bit\n      A[k][k] += 1e-8;\n    }\n    if(pivot !== k){\n      [A[k], A[pivot]] = [A[pivot], A[k]];\n      [b[k], b[pivot]] = [b[pivot], b[k]];\n    }\n    const akk = A[k][k];\n    for(let i=k+1;i<n;i++){\n      const factor = A[i][k] / (akk || 1e-12);\n      b[i] -= factor * b[k];\n      for(let j=k;j<n;j++){\n        A[i][j] -= factor * A[k][j];\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  const x = Array(n).fill(0);\n  for(let i=n-1;i>=0;i--){\n    let s = b[i];\n    for(let j=i+1;j<n;j++) s -= A[i][j]*x[j];\n    x[i] = s / (A[i][i] || 1e-12);\n  }\n  return x;\n}\n\n// Build Vandermonde design matrix for x array and degree d (columns: x^0 ... x^d)\nfunction vandermonde(xs, d) {\n  const n = xs.length;\n  const A = Array.from({length:n}, ()=>Array(d+1));\n  for(let i=0;i<n;i++){\n    let val = 1;\n    for(let j=0;j<=d;j++){\n      A[i][j]=val;\n      val *= xs[i];\n    }\n  }\n  return A;\n}\n\n// Fit polynomial via normal equations with optional ridge regularization λ\nfunction fitPoly(xs, ys, degree, lambda=0) {\n  const A = vandermonde(xs, degree);\n  const At = transpose(A);\n  const AtA = matMul(At, A); // (d+1)x(d+1)\n  const n = AtA.length;\n  const AtAreg = AtA.map((r,i)=>r.map((v,j)=> v + (i===j ? lambda : 0) ));\n  const Aty = matVecMul(At, ys); // (d+1) vector\n  const coeffs = solveLinear(AtAreg, Aty); // length d+1\n  return coeffs;\n}\nfunction predictPoly(coeffs, xs) {\n  const d = coeffs.length - 1;\n  return xs.map(x => {\n    let val = 0, pow=1;\n    for(let j=0;j<=d;j++){\n      val += coeffs[j]*pow;\n      pow *= x;\n    }\n    return val;\n  });\n}\nfunction mse(a,b){\n  let s=0;\n  for(let i=0;i<a.length;i++){ const e=a[i]-b[i]; s+=e*e; }\n  return s/a.length;\n}\n\n// ==== Demo: data generation and plotting ====\n\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('plot');\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\nconst width = canvas.width;\nconst height = canvas.height;\nconst pad = {l:44, r:12, t:12, b:36};\n\nlet state = {\n  degree: 3,\n  nSamples: 30,\n  noise: 0.2,\n  trainPct: 0.7,\n  lambda: 0,\n  xs: [],\n  ys: [],\n  trainIdx: [],\n  testIdx: [],\n  trueFuncName: 'sin'\n};\n\n// True function (ground truth)\nfunction trueFunction(x) {\n  // Example non-linear function on [-1,1]\n  // a mixture of sin and polynomial to be interesting\n  return Math.sin(2.0 * x * Math.PI) * (0.6 + 0.4 * x) + 0.3 * x*x - 0.15 * x;\n}\n\n// Generate data\nfunction generateData() {\n  const n = state.nSamples;\n  const xs = [];\n  const ys = [];\n  for(let i=0;i<n;i++){\n    // sample x uniformly in [-1,1]\n    const x = -1 + 2*Math.random();\n    const ytrue = trueFunction(x);\n    const y = ytrue + randn()*state.noise;\n    xs.push(x);\n    ys.push(y);\n  }\n  // split into train/test\n  const indices = xs.map((_,i)=>i);\n  shuffle(indices);\n  const nTrain = Math.max(3, Math.round(state.trainPct/100 * n));\n  const trainIdx = indices.slice(0, nTrain);\n  const testIdx  = indices.slice(nTrain);\n  state.xs = xs; state.ys = ys;\n  state.trainIdx = trainIdx; state.testIdx = testIdx;\n}\n\n// random normal (Box-Muller)\nfunction randn(){\n  let u=0,v=0;\n  while(u===0) u=Math.random();\n  while(v===0) v=Math.random();\n  return Math.sqrt(-2.0*Math.log(u)) * Math.cos(2*Math.PI*v);\n}\nfunction shuffle(a){\n  for(let i=a.length-1;i>0;i--){\n    const j = Math.floor(Math.random()*(i+1));\n    [a[i], a[j]] = [a[j], a[i]];\n  }\n}\n\n// Draw everything\nfunction draw() {\n  // clear\n  ctx.clearRect(0,0,width,height);\n  // axes area\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#fff\";\n  ctx.fillRect(0,0,width,height);\n\n  // compute plotting range\n  const xsAll = state.xs.slice();\n  const xMin = -1.05, xMax = 1.05;\n  // y range: include true function and data\n  let yMin = Infinity, yMax = -Infinity;\n  // include dense true curve\n  for(let i=0;i<=200;i++){\n    const x = xMin + (xMax-xMin)*i/200;\n    const y = trueFunction(x);\n    if(y<yMin) yMin = y;\n    if(y>yMax) yMax = y;\n  }\n  for(let y of state.ys){ if(y<yMin) yMin=y; if(y>yMax) yMax=y; }\n  // pad\n  const yPad = Math.max(0.2, 0.08*(yMax-yMin));\n  const yLo = yMin - yPad, yHi = yMax + yPad;\n\n  // transform coordinates\n  function tx(x){ return pad.l + (x - xMin) / (xMax - xMin) * (width - pad.l - pad.r); }\n  function ty(y){ return pad.t + (yHi - y) / (yHi - yLo) * (height - pad.t - pad.b); }\n\n  // grid lines and axes\n  ctx.strokeStyle = \"#e9eefb\";\n  ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n  for(let gx=-1; gx<=1; gx+=0.5){\n    const x = tx(gx);\n    ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(x, pad.t); ctx.lineTo(x, height-pad.b); ctx.stroke();\n  }\n  for(let gy=Math.floor(yLo*10)/10; gy<=yHi; gy+= (yHi-yLo)/6 ){\n    const y = ty(gy);\n    ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pad.l, y); ctx.lineTo(width-pad.r, y); ctx.stroke();\n  }\n  // axes lines\n  ctx.strokeStyle = \"#bfcddb\";\n  ctx.lineWidth = 1.2;\n  // x axis at y=0 if visible\n  if(yLo <= 0 && yHi >= 0){\n    ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(pad.l, ty(0)); ctx.lineTo(width-pad.r, ty(0)); ctx.stroke();\n  }\n  // y axis at x=0 if visible\n  if(xMin <= 0 && xMax >= 0){\n    ctx.beginPath(); ctx.moveTo(tx(0), pad.t); ctx.lineTo(tx(0), height-pad.b); ctx.stroke();\n  }\n\n  // draw true function (gray smooth)\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  for(let i=0;i<=400;i++){\n    const x = xMin + (xMax-xMin)*i/400;\n    const y = trueFunction(x);\n    const px = tx(x), py = ty(y);\n    if(i===0) ctx.moveTo(px,py); else ctx.lineTo(px,py);\n  }\n  ctx.strokeStyle = \"#888c94\";\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n  ctx.stroke();\n\n  // Fit polynomial using training data\n  const xsTrain = state.trainIdx.map(i=>state.xs[i]);\n  const ysTrain = state.trainIdx.map(i=>state.ys[i]);\n  const xsTest  = state.testIdx.map(i=>state.xs[i]);\n  const ysTest  = state.testIdx.map(i=>state.ys[i]);\n\n  const coeffs = fitPoly(xsTrain, ysTrain, state.degree, state.lambda);\n\n  // plot fitted curve (green)\n  const curveX = [];\n  for(let i=0;i<=400;i++) curveX.push(xMin + (xMax-xMin)*i/400);\n  const curveY = predictPoly(coeffs, curveX);\n  ctx.beginPath();\n  for(let i=0;i<curveX.length;i++){\n    const px = tx(curveX[i]), py = ty(curveY[i]);\n    if(i===0) ctx.moveTo(px,py); else ctx.lineTo(px,py);\n  }\n  ctx.strokeStyle = \"#2aa450\"; // green\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2.6;\n  ctx.stroke();\n\n  // draw training points (blue)\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#2b7fff\";\n  for(let i=0;i<xsTrain.length;i++){\n    const px = tx(xsTrain[i]), py = ty(ysTrain[i]);\n    circle(px,py,4);\n  }\n  // draw test points (red)\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#ff3b3b\";\n  for(let i=0;i<xsTest.length;i++){\n    const px = tx(xsTest[i]), py = ty(ysTest[i]);\n    circle(px,py,4);\n  }\n\n  // small axes labels\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#333\";\n  ctx.font = \"12px sans-serif\";\n  ctx.textAlign = \"center\";\n  ctx.fillText(\"x\", width/2, height - 6);\n  ctx.save();\n  ctx.translate(12, height/2);\n  ctx.rotate(-Math.PI/2);\n  ctx.textAlign = \"center\";\n  ctx.fillText(\"y\", 0, 0);\n  ctx.restore();\n\n  // show legend dots\n  ctx.font = \"12px sans-serif\";\n  ctx.textAlign = \"left\";\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#111\";\n  ctx.fillText(\"Fitted (polynomial)\", pad.l+4, pad.t+14);\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#2aa450\"; ctx.fillRect(pad.l+120, pad.t+5, 18, 8);\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#111\";\n  ctx.fillText(\"True function\", pad.l+4, pad.t+28);\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#888c94\"; ctx.fillRect(pad.l+120, pad.t+19, 18, 8);\n\n  // compute metrics\n  const yPredTrain = predictPoly(coeffs, xsTrain);\n  const yPredTest = predictPoly(coeffs, xsTest);\n  const trainErr = mse(yPredTrain, ysTrain);\n  const testErr = ysTest.length>0 ? mse(yPredTest, ysTest) : NaN;\n\n  document.getElementById('trainMse').innerText = trainErr.toFixed(4);\n  document.getElementById('testMse').innerText = isNaN(testErr) ? \"-\" : testErr.toFixed(4);\n\n  // show coefficients summary (small)\n  ctx.fillStyle = \"#333\";\n  ctx.font = \"11px monospace\";\n  ctx.textAlign = \"right\";\n  let coeffStr = coeffs.slice(0,6).map((c,i)=> (i===0? \"\" : \" \") + c.toFixed(3)).join(\",\");\n  if(coeffs.length>6) coeffStr += \" ...\";\n  ctx.fillText(\"coeffs: [\" + coeffStr + \"]\", width - 8, height - 10);\n}\n\n// helper: draw filled circle\nfunction circle(x,y,r){\n  ctx.beginPath(); ctx.arc(x,y,r,0,Math.PI*2); ctx.fill();\n}\n\n// ==== UI interactions ====\nconst degSlider = document.getElementById('degree');\nconst degVal = document.getElementById('degVal');\nconst nSamples = document.getElementById('nSamples');\nconst nSamplesVal = document.getElementById('nSamplesVal');\nconst noiseS = document.getElementById('noise');\nconst noiseVal = document.getElementById('noiseVal');\nconst trainPct = document.getElementById('trainPct');\nconst trainPctVal = document.getElementById('trainPctVal');\nconst lambdaS = document.getElementById('lambda');\nconst lambdaVal = document.getElementById('lambdaVal');\nconst regen = document.getElementById('regen');\nconst reset = document.getElementById('reset');\n\nfunction updateStateFromUI(){\n  state.degree = parseInt(degSlider.value,10);\n  state.nSamples = parseInt(nSamples.value,10);\n  state.noise = parseFloat(noiseS.value);\n  state.trainPct = parseInt(trainPct.value,10);\n  state.lambda = parseFloat(lambdaS.value);\n\n  degVal.innerText = state.degree;\n  nSamplesVal.innerText = state.nSamples;\n  noiseVal.innerText = state.noise.toFixed(2);\n  trainPctVal.innerText = state.trainPct + \"%\";\n  lambdaVal.innerText = state.lambda.toFixed(2);\n}\n\ndegSlider.addEventListener('input', ()=>{ updateStateFromUI(); draw(); });\nnSamples.addEventListener('input', ()=>{ updateStateFromUI(); });\nnoiseS.addEventListener('input', ()=>{ updateStateFromUI(); });\ntrainPct.addEventListener('input', ()=>{ updateStateFromUI(); });\nlambdaS.addEventListener('input', ()=>{ updateStateFromUI(); draw(); });\n\nregen.addEventListener('click', ()=>{ updateStateFromUI(); generateData(); draw(); });\nreset.addEventListener('click', ()=>{\n  degSlider.value = 3; nSamples.value = 30; noiseS.value = 0.2; trainPct.value = 70; lambdaS.value = 0;\n  updateStateFromUI();\n  generateData();\n  draw();\n});\n\n// initialize\nupdateStateFromUI();\ngenerateData();\ndraw();\n\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
